Package: DNABarcodeCompatibility
Type: Package
Title: A tool for optimizing combinations of compatible DNA barcodes used in Next Generation Sequencing experiments on 4-, 2-, and 1-channel Illumina sequencers
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Céline Trébeau
Maintainer: Céline Trébeau <celine.trebeau@pasteur.fr>
Authors@R: c(
    person("Céline", "Trébeau", email = "celine.trebeau@pasteur.fr", role = "aut"),
    person("Jacques", "Boutet de Monvel", email = "jacques.boutet-de-monvel@pasteur.fr", role = "ctb"),
    person("Raphaël", "Etournay", email = "raphael.etournay@pasteur.fr", role = "ctb"))
Description: The package allows one to obtain an optimized combination of compatible DNA barcodes to be used for multiplex sequencing. The user inputs a list of available DNA barcodes, the total number of libraries to be sequenced and the number of libraries to be multiplexed. The resulting output consists of a set of least redundant and compatible DNA barcodes.
